OL,3,CBlack women ignored and 'not taken
OL,4,Cseriously' in maternity care, MPs say
OL,6,FPaulette Hamilton, acting chairwoman
OL,7,Fof the Health and Social Care
OL,8,FCommittee, said: "Safe maternal care
OL,9,Ffor black women depends on a workforce
OL,10,Fthat listens to, understands and
OL,11,Frespects their needs.
OL,13,F"For that to happen, maternal services
OL,14,Fmust be properly prepared, equipped
OL,15,Fand resourced.
OL,17,F"Leadership must be effective but it
OL,18,Fmust also be accountable. This report
OL,19,Fproves that this is not, currently,
OL,20,Fthe case."
