OL,3,CBlack women ignored and 'not taken
OL,4,Cseriously' in maternity care, MPs say
OL,6,FThe committee has urged healthcare
OL,7,Fbodies to introduce mandatory cultural
OL,8,Fcompetency training, putting the
OL,9,Fexperience of black women "at the
OL,10,Fcentre" of efforts to "better
OL,11,Funderstand the perspective of others".
OL,13,FBaroness Amos, who is leading the
OL,14,Finvestigation, will make national
OL,15,Frecommendations for improvements, said
OL,16,F"it is vital" that the experiences of
OL,17,Fmothers and affected families are at
OL,18,Fthe heart of the investigation from
OL,19,Fits "very beginning" and are "fully
OL,20,Fheard".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
