OL,3,CBlack women ignored and 'not taken
OL,4,Cseriously' in maternity care, MPs say
OL,6,FMeanwhile, an NHS spokesperson
OL,7,Fdescribed the disparity in care for
OL,8,Fblack mothers and their children as
OL,9,F"unacceptable".
OL,11,FThe spokesperson said: "While the NHS
OL,12,Fhas made improvements in reducing
OL,13,Finequalities within maternity
OL,14,Fservices, there is more work to be
OL,15,Fdone, and with the rollout of
OL,16,Finitiatives such as the Maternal Care
OL,17,FBundle and the Equity and Anti-
OL,18,FDiscrimination Programme we want to
OL,19,Fensure all women receive high-quality
OL,20,Fcare throughout their pregnancy."
